PHP SAPI module for Virtuoso
============================

This is a SAPI module for PHP 4.x and 5.x,
implemented as a Virtuoso loadable module.


Building:

  To build the plugin, you need to build a static libphpX.a,
  configured with ZTS.

  In the php source directory, execute something similar to

  [PHP 5]
	./configure \
		--prefix=/where/to/put/it \
		--enable-maintainer-zts \
		--with-tsrm-pthreads \
		--with-config-file-path=. \
		--enable-static \
		--disable-shared \
		--disable-ipv6 \
		--enable-embed=static \
		--with-iodbc=/usr \
		--with-zlib \
		--without-mysql \
		--without-pear \
		--disable-cli \
		--disable-cgi

  [PHP 4]
	./configure \
		--prefix=/where/to/put/it \
		--enable-experimental-zts \
		--with-tsrm-pthreads \
		--with-config-file-path=. \
		--enable-static \
		--disable-shared \
		--disable-ipv6 \
		--enable-embed=static \
		--with-iodbc=/usr \
		--with-zlib \
		--without-mysql \
		--without-pear \
		--disable-cli \
		--disable-cgi


Installation:

1. Register the plugin in your virtuoso.ini:

    [Plugins]
    ..
    Load10 = Hosting, hosting_php.so

2. Copy the php.ini-recommended from the php distro to the same directory
   as your virtuoso.ini.
   Alternatively, you can set the PHP_INI_PATH environment variable to the
   full path of the php.ini file to use.


[Code by Paul Nieuwdorp, Oct 2007]
